<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-08-28T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-08-28T17:00:00-05:00" n="704" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d704">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">875.001Zog/12: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Albania</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hart</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-08-28T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August 28,
                                        1928—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>28. Your 48, August 4, 10 a.m. The Department presumes you will continue
                            to keep it advised by cable regarding the proposed change of regime in
                            Albania. The Department also wishes information at the appropriate
                            moment regarding the action your colleagues will take concerning
                            recognition and presence at the coronation.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>